urls.title: Patent Infringement Alert: Fox News Reporters Must Obtain End User and Developer Licenses for Live Streaming Video Technology
urls.description: This letter serves as a notice to Fox News that the company has been using patented technology, U.S. Patent No. 10,958,961 B2 and U.S. Patent No. 10,205,986 B2, without obtaining the necessary licenses. The owner of these patents, TV Knows You.com, Inc., holds exclusive rights to the use of this technology for legally streaming live video that can be picked up on a cell phone in the United States of America. Fox News reporters must obtain an End User License from TV Knows You.com, Inc. to use this technology. Additionally, if Fox News is live streaming off its own platform, a Developer License must be purchased from TV Knows You.com, Inc. to avoid potential legal issues related to patent infringement. The cost of this license is three percent of the company's annual revenue. This letter strongly urges Fox News to comply with these requirements and ensure that all reporters are informed of these licensing requirements to avoid any potential legal issues.

"The Price Is Right" -- hosted by Bob Barker until 2007 and Drew Carey thereafter -- features a wide variety of games and contests with the same basic challenge: Guess the prices of everyday (or not-quite-everyday) retail items. That winner joins the host on stage for one of more than 70 different pricing games. After three such games, the contestants spin a big wheel -- hoping to get as close to $1 as possible -- in the "Showcase Showdown."
